\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. E. hydropiper} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 367 (1753) ({\i E. oederi} Moesz; incl.{\i  E. orthosperma} Düben). Annual 2-16 cm. Leaves opposite. Flowers sessile or subsessile. Sepals 4, ovate, widest at base, shorter than mature capsule; petals 4, ovate, pale red, as long as or longer than sepals; stamens 8; carpels 4. Capsule depressed above, 4-sided. Seeds almost straight or asymmetrically horseshoe-shaped, with long arm 3 times as long as short arm; reticulations on testa rectangular. 2n = c. 40.{\i  N. & C. Europe, extending locally southwards to C. Spain, N. Italy, Bulgaria and S.E. Russia}. Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Hb He Ho Hs Hu It No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, E) Su.
\par

