\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. E. triandra} Schkuhr,{\i  Handb.}{\b  1}: 345 (1791) (incl. {\i E. callitrichoides} (W. Nyl.) Kaufm.). Annual 1-18 cm. Leaves opposite. Flowers sessile. Sepals (2-)3(-4), obtuse, widest at base; petals 3, white or red, longer than sepals, sometimes absent in submerged plants; stamens 3, opposite sepals; carpels 3. Capsule remaining in leaf-axils at maturity. Seeds slightly curved. 2n = c. 40.{\i  C., N. & E. Europe, extending to C. France and N. Italy.} Au Az Be Bu Cz Fe Ga Ge Ho Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, E) Su.
